      <section eId="sec_2994_BB">
        <num>2994-BB</num>
        <heading>General provisions</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_2994_BB__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Emergency medical services\npersonnel, home care services agency personnel, hospice personnel, and\nhospital emergency services personnel shall honor nonhospital orders not\nto resuscitate, except as provided in section twenty-nine hundred\nninety-four-ee of this article.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_2994_BB__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>A nonhospital order not to resuscitate shall not constitute an\norder to withhold or withdraw treatment other than cardiopulmonary\nresuscitation.\n  2. A nonhospital order not to resuscitate may be issued during\nhospitalization to take effect after hospitalization, or may be issued\nfor a person who is not a patient in, or a resident of, a hospital.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
